\title{Depth Search}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Deep multi-source research combining academic MCPs (arxiv, semantic-scholar, paper-search, deepwiki), Exa semantic search, and local ~/.topos knowledge base. Use for comprehensive research requiring multiple sources. NEVER fall back to web_search - ask user for help instead.}

\subtree{
\title{Depth Search}
\p{Comprehensive multi-source research skill. Searches across academic databases, semantic web search, and local knowledge before asking the user for help.}

\subtree{
\title{Search Order}
\p{Execute searches in this order, using parallel subagents where possible:}

\subtree{
\title{1. Local Knowledge Base (~/.topos)}
\p{Search \code{\startverb ~/.topos\stopverb} directory first for existing research, notes, and cached data:}

\ul{
\li{Use \code{\startverb glob\stopverb} and \code{\startverb Grep\stopverb} to find relevant files}
\li{Check \code{\startverb .md\stopverb}, \code{\startverb .org\stopverb}, \code{\startverb .jl\stopverb}, \code{\startverb .py\stopverb}, \code{\startverb .json\stopverb} files}
\li{Look in subdirectories: \code{\startverb skills/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb archived/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb Gay.jl/\stopverb}, etc.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Academic MCPs (parallel)}
\p{Launch parallel subagents to search all 4 academic sources:}

\pre{\startverb
| MCP | Tools | Best For |
|-----|-------|----------|
| **arxiv** | `search_papers`, `get_paper`, `download_paper` | Preprints, CS/physics/math papers |
| **semantic-scholar** | `paper_relevance_search`, `paper_details`, `paper_citations` | Citation analysis, author profiles |
| **paper-search** | `search_arxiv`, `search_pubmed`, `search_biorxiv`, etc. | Multi-source aggregation |
| **deepwiki** | `read_wiki_structure`, `read_wiki_contents`, `ask_question` | GitHub repo documentation |
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Exa Semantic Search}
\p{Use Exa MCP for high-quality web search:}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb web_search_exa\stopverb} - Semantic web search}
\li{\code{\startverb crawling_exa\stopverb} - Extract web content}
\li{\code{\startverb company_research_exa\stopverb} - Company research}
\li{\code{\startverb deep_researcher_start\stopverb} / \code{\startverb deep_researcher_check\stopverb} - Deep research tasks}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Ask User for Help}
\p{If all sources fail to find what's needed:}

\ul{
\li{\strong{DO NOT fall back to \code{\startverb web_search\stopverb}} - it's basic keyword matching only}
\li{Instead, ask the user:}
\li{"I couldn't find [X] in academic databases, Exa, or local files. Can you provide a link, paper title, or more context?"}
\li{Suggest specific sources they might check manually}
\li{Offer to try different search terms}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Critical Rules}
\ol{
\li{\strong{NEVER use \code{\startverb web_search\stopverb} as a fallback} - it's not equivalent to Exa}
\li{\strong{NEVER use \code{\startverb web_search\stopverb} in Task subagents} - use Exa tools instead}
\li{\strong{Always search local ~/.topos first} - may have cached/annotated versions}
\li{\strong{Use parallel subagents} for academic MCPs to maximize speed}
\li{\strong{Ask user for help} rather than guessing or using inferior search}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Example Workflow}
\pre{\startverb
User: "Find papers on world models for LLMs"

1. Search ~/.topos for existing notes/papers
2. Launch 4 parallel Task subagents:
   - arxiv: search_papers("world models LLM")
   - semantic-scholar: paper_relevance_search("world models language models")
   - paper-search: search across all sources
   - deepwiki: check relevant GitHub repos
3. If needed, use Exa: web_search_exa("world models LLM research")
4. Synthesize results from all sources
5. If still not found: ask user for clarification
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Parallel Subagent Template}
\p{When searching academic sources, use this pattern:}

\pre{\startverb
Launch 4 parallel Task subagents:
- Task 1: Use arxiv MCP to search for [query]
- Task 2: Use semantic-scholar MCP to search for [query]  
- Task 3: Use paper-search MCP to search for [query]
- Task 4: Use deepwiki MCP to find related repos/docs
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{What NOT To Do}
\p{❌ \code{\startverb web_search\stopverb} as fallback when Exa fails ❌ Single-source search when multiple are available ❌ Skipping local ~/.topos search ❌ Guessing answers without exhausting sources ❌ Sequential searches when parallel is possible}
}

\subtree{
\title{What TO Do}
\p{✅ Search ~/.topos first for cached knowledge ✅ Parallel subagents for academic MCPs ✅ Exa for semantic web search ✅ Ask user when sources are exhausted ✅ Synthesize results from multiple sources}
}
}